<pre><code>if(originalRect_.size.height > originalRect_.size.width) {
      CGFloat tempValue = originalRect_.size.height;
       originalRect_.size.height = originalRect_.size.width;
       originalRect_.size.width = tempValue;
}</pre></code>
游戏的屏幕可以被正常推到上面，但是键盘的弹出方向会出现问题
1. 手机横屏状态且屏幕方向不锁定，键盘横屏弹出
2. 手机竖屏无论屏幕方向锁不锁定，键盘竖屏弹出
3. 手机横屏且屏幕方向锁定，键盘竖屏弹出。

请给位帮忙解答？

I have some image views in ccui.HBox (for example, this bug works with all layout types). 
Some of them has scale != 1. 
And their position on screen is like they doesn't have scale transformation.
![2015-11-11 10 15 13](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10628482/11085978/862bee2e-885d-11e5-87d3-f4e94f9b43cf.png)
(Code examples are in JS, but it reproduces both in C++ ant JS versions)

``` javascript
var HelloWorldLayer = ccui.Layout.extend({
    ctor:function () {
        this._super();

        this.setContentSize(cc.director.getWinSize());

        var layout = new ccui.HBox();

        var sprite1 = new ccui.ImageView(res.HelloWorld_png);

        var parameter = new ccui.LinearLayoutParameter();
        parameter.setGravity(ccui.LinearLayoutParameter.BOTTOM);

        sprite1.setLayoutParameter(parameter);

        var sprite2 = sprite1.clone();
        sprite2.setScale(0.5);

        sprite2.setLayoutParameter(parameter.clone());

        layout.addChild(sprite1);
        layout.addChild(sprite2);

        layout.setContentSize(sprite1.width + sprite2.width, sprite1.height);

        this.addChild(layout);
    }
});
```

Is it a but or a feature(layout manager must work like this and i must consider this behavior in my code)?

If it is a bug, an obvious solution is to apply transform(node to parent) to content size of child widgets in **doLayout** method of LayoutManager's like this(example in JS version, but it can be applied to C++ version):

``` javascript
